@startuml
title Mandatory Access Control (MAC)

hide circle
hide empty members
skinparam backgroundColor transparent

class Subject {
  +subjectId: String
  +name: String
  +clearanceLevel: SecurityLevel
}

class Object {
  +objectId: String
  +name: String
  +classificationLevel: SecurityLevel
}

enum SecurityLevel {
  Unclassified
  Confidential
  Secret
  TopSecret
}

class PolicyRule {
  +canRead(subject, object): Boolean
  +canWrite(subject, object): Boolean
}

Subject --> SecurityLevel : clearance
Object --> SecurityLevel : classification
PolicyRule ..> Subject
PolicyRule ..> Object

note bottom of PolicyRule
Access is determined by
central policy and labels,
not by the object owner.
Example:
"No read up, no write down"
end note

note left of Subject
- user
- process
- running program
end note


@enduml